{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"DIAGNOSIS of the 2 unmasked clean-wheel failures (both pre-existing, from story\nauthorial-hated-blackbear; hidden by the import bug until Gerrit 529 let the\ndegradation-path pytest step run):\n\n1. CLI review-code exit code (test_cli_operation_degrades_without_extra[review_code]):\n   The library review_code() correctly returns the inert disabled result\n   {findings:[], runner:\"code-review-disabled\", summary:\"...disabled...\"} with no raise\n   — my failure.py fix is fine. But the CLI `rebar review-code` maps that result to\n   exit 1 via _disposition_exit_code (no `verdict`, no `coverage.retryable` -> generic\n   non-PASS -> 1). For an off-by-default fail-safe capability it must be exit 0.\n   FIX: _review_code returns 0 for the disabled code-review result.\n\n2. verify_completion \"DID NOT RAISE\" (test_mcp_operations_error_cleanly_when_gated_on_\n   but_extra_absent): verify_completion intentionally catches LLMError and returns\n   _structured_llm_failure(exc) = {error:\"...agents...\", resolution_class:\n   NEEDS_INVESTIGATION, retryable:False, diagnostic:{...}} — a structured degrade, NOT\n   a raise. THREE MCP tools do this (review_code, verify_completion, review_plan);\n   review_ticket/scan_spec raise. The test's must-raise `forced` set exempts review_code\n   (comment) but forgot verify_completion. It is a STALE test, not a code bug (the close\n   gate consumes this structured verdict and fail-closes correctly —\n   test_gate_missing_llm_fails_closed passes).\n   FIX: exempt verify_completion from the must-raise set and assert its structured-degrade\n   contract (error surfaces 'agents', resolution_class present, not silent/empty).\n\nBoth will be verified in a true no-extras clean venv (where these tests actually run;\nthey SKIP when the agents extra is present, which is why my first local run missed them).\nLanding as a second change stacked on 529."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783787686698800001,"uuid":"d5d8619b-da0e-4424-8ecf-703b3e5eba74"}